  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Endometrial injury performed in a cycle preceding the one for embryo transfer is associated
      with an increased implantation and pregnancy rate when carried out during the month preceding
      that of ovulation induction and fresh embryo transfer. However, there is no evidence about
      the effect of this intervention on the transfer of cryopreserved embryos.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
